<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-10-15T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-10-15T15:00:00-05:00" n="467" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d467">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">861.01/134: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Consul General at Irkutsk</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_HEL1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Harris</hi></persName>), <hi rend="italic">temporarily at Omsk</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-10-15T16:00:00-04:00"><hi rend="italic">October 15,
                                        1919, 4 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>The President’s serious illness precludes for the time being the
                            possibility of a decision as to the matters discussed in your 386, <pb facs="0554" n="442" xml:id="pg_442"/> September 19, 5 p.m.,<note n="86" xml:id="d467fn86">Transmitted in telegram from the Chargé in
                                China, Sept. 22, <ref target="#pg_427">p. 427</ref>.</note> but they
                            will be taken up at the earliest possible moment.</p>
                        <closer><signed><persName corresp="#p_LR1"><hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi></persName></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>